{#
  ============================================================================
  TEMPLATE: observation-resultslab-eu-lab_fsh.twig
  ============================================================================
  PURPOSE
    A FRAME TEMPLATE that generates a FSH Observation instance conforming to
    the ObservationResultsLaboratoryEu profile (EU Laboratory Report). It
    provides the instance header and the fixed laboratory category, then
    delegates all remaining body rules to the shared partial:

      {% include 'observation-medical-test-body.fsh.twig' %}

    This is the simpler of the two frame templates that include the shared
    body partial — it has a single fixed category (laboratory) and no
    conditional branching on observation type.

  RELATIONSHIP TO observation-medical-test-result-eu_fsh.twig
    Both templates include observation-medical-test-body.fsh.twig. The
    differences are:

    ┌────────────────────────────────┬────────────────────────────┬───────────────────────────────┐
    │ Aspect                         │ resultslab-eu-lab          │ medical-test-result-eu        │
    ├────────────────────────────────┼────────────────────────────┼───────────────────────────────┤
    │ Profile                        │ ObservationResultsLaboratoryEu│ MedicalTestResultEuCore    │
    │ Category                       │ Fixed: laboratory [slice]  │ Conditional on boolean flags  │
    │ Category branching             │ None                       │ isVitaLSignCode / isImagingCode│
    │                                │                            │ / isLaboratory / default      │
    │ Performer display              │ Fixed: "Central European   │ Varies by category branch      │
    │                                │  Laboratory"               │                               │
    └────────────────────────────────┴────────────────────────────┴───────────────────────────────┘

  PROFILE CONFORMANCE
    InstanceOf: ObservationResultsLaboratoryEu

  FIXED ELEMENTS (frame only)
    category[laboratory].coding = $observation-category#laboratory
    performer[+].display        = "The Central European Laboratory"
    The performer Reference (to a fixed UUID) is commented out — retained
    for future use when a real performer resource is available.

  INCLUDE PATTERN
    `{% include 'observation-medical-test-body.fsh.twig' %}` passes the full
    current Twig variable context without restriction. All labresult.*
    variables and instanceid must be supplied by the PHP caller. The included
    partial also supplies the %%HEAD%% and %%HTML%% section markers.

  CONTEXT VARIABLES
  ┌──────────────────┬──────────┬──────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
  │ Variable         │ Type     │ Description                                      │
  ├──────────────────┼──────────┼──────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ instanceid       │ string   │ Resource id; used in setInstance() and in the    │
  │                  │          │ included partial's * id rule.                    │
  │ labresult.*      │ various  │ All lab result fields consumed by the included   │
  │                  │          │ partial. See observation-medical-test-body_fsh   │
  │                  │          │ .twig for the full variable contract.            │
  └──────────────────┴──────────┴──────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

  CODESYSTEMS REFERENCED (frame only)
    $observation-category — #laboratory

  AUTHOR   KH
  SINCE    2025-09-02
  ============================================================================
#}

%%FSH%% {# ── Section marker required by the FSH pre-processor ─────────────── #}

Instance: {{ setInstance("Instance-Observation-" ~ instanceid) }}
InstanceOf: ObservationResultsLaboratoryEu
Title: "Observation Results Laboratory"
Description: "Observation Results Laboratory"
Usage: #inline

{#
  ── Fixed laboratory category ───────────────────────────────────────────────
  Named [laboratory] slice is required by the ObservationResultsLaboratoryEu
  profile. Performer display is hardcoded; the Reference is commented out
  pending integration of real performer resources.
#}
* category[laboratory].coding = $observation-category#laboratory
* performer[+].display        = "The Central European Laboratory"
{# * performer[=] = Reference(urn:uuid:e512e2e2-9600-4c69-a269-af3ab5421e09) #}

{#
  ── Include shared observation body ─────────────────────────────────────────
  Supplies all remaining FSH rules, HTML bag operations, text.div, and the
  %%HEAD%% / %%HTML%% section markers.
#}
{% include 'observation-medical-test-body.fsh.twig' %}
